# Python / ML

## Stack

`torch`, `transformers`, `librosa`, `scikit-learn`, `pandas`, `fastapi`, `joblib`

## Default encoder

`BSC-LT/hubert-base-ca-2k` with mean+std pooling (1536-d). Wav2Vec2 is experimental only.

## Inference artifact

- Path: `models/cv26-hubert-svm-calibrated/`
- Backend loads encoder + `model.joblib`; response must match `AccentOracleResult` in `web/src/lib/accentOracleClient.ts`

## Data rules

- Split by **speaker ID**, never by clip
- CV26: prefer `train.tsv`, `variant` label, exclude `Tortosí` unless policy changes
- Write evaluation results to `reports/` with reproducible CLI commands

## Scripts pattern

CLI scripts in `scripts/` use `argparse`, write manifests to `manifests/`, outputs to `data/` or `embeddings/` (local only).
